data.name: Quinoa and Black Bean Stuffed Bell Peppers
data.quickTastyDescription: Healthy and colorful bell peppers filled with a protein-packed quinoa and black bean mix, perfect for a nutritious meal!
detailedCookingInstructions: Cut the tops off the bell peppers and remove the seeds.
In a large bowl, combine cooked quinoa, black beans, corn, diced tomatoes, chili powder, cumin, and salt. Mix well.
Stuff each bell pepper with the quinoa mixture and place them upright in a baking dish.
Drizzle olive oil over the stuffed peppers and cover the dish with foil.
Bake in the preheated oven for 25 minutes. If using cheese, remove the foil, sprinkle cheese on top, and bake for an additional 5-7 minutes until the cheese is melted and bubbly.
Remove from the oven, let cool slightly, and serve.

data.modifiersForBase: Filled with a nutritious quinoa and bean mixture
